# tanh^c5 with c5 even: symmetric, always positive
# tanh^c5 with c5 odd: antisymmetric
# For aggregation: use tanh^2 (always 0->1) or just tanh with shift
# tanh(u) goes from -1 to 1; tanh(u)^2 goes from 0 to 1 (but symmetric around 0)

# Better: (1+tanh(u))/2 is logistic, equivalent to 1/(1+exp(-2u))
# Try: c4 * ((1+tanh(c0*x1^c1*(x0-c2*x1^c3)))/2)^c5 + c6
