h_rich_simpler)}')\n\n# Try: tanh-Richards with log concentration scaling\nrate_log = c0 + c1 * sp.log(x1)\nhalf_time_log = c2 + c3 * sp.log(x1)\ngrowth5 = rate_log * (x0 - half_time_log)\nexpr_tanh_rich_log = c4 * ((1 + sp.tanh(growth5)) / 2)**c5 + c6\nprint(f'tanh-Richards log scaling (7 const): complexity={complexity(expr_tanh_rich_log)}')\n\n# What about: exp-Richards with power-law (original Richards form)\n# y = c4 / (1 + exp(-c0*x1^c1*(x0 - c2*x1^c3)))^c5 + c6\nexpr_rich_pow = c4 / (1 + sp.exp(-rate * (x0 - half_time)))**c5 + c6\nprint(f'exp-Richards power-law (7 const): complexity={complexity(expr_rich_pow)}')\n\"\n"
